.TH "ELEMENT.CLASSLIST" "3JS" "November 25, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
Element.classList \- Element: classList property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The read\-only \f[B]\f[CB]classList\f[B]\f[R] property of the
\f[CR]Element\f[R] interface contains a live \f[CR]DOMTokenList\f[R]
collection representing the \f[CR]class\f[R] attribute of the element.
This can then be used to manipulate the class list.
.PP
Using \f[CR]classList\f[R] is a convenient alternative to accessing an
element\(cqs list of classes as a space\-delimited string via
\f[CR]element.className\f[R].
.SH VALUE
A \f[CR]DOMTokenList\f[R] object representing the contents of the
element\(cqs \f[CR]class\f[R] attribute.
If the \f[CR]class\f[R] attribute is not set or empty, it returns an
empty \f[CR]DOMTokenList\f[R], i.e., a \f[CR]DOMTokenList\f[R] with the
\f[CR]length\f[R] property equal to \f[CR]0\f[R].
.PP
Although the \f[CR]classList\f[R] property itself is read\-only in the
sense that you can\(cqt replace the \f[CR]DOMTokenList\f[R] object, you
can still assign to the \f[CR]classList\f[R] property directly, which is
equivalent to assigning to its \f[CR]value\f[R] property.
You can also modify the \f[CR]DOMTokenList\f[R] object using the
\f[CR]add()\f[R], \f[CR]remove()\f[R], \f[CR]replace()\f[R], and
\f[CR]toggle()\f[R] methods.
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] div = document.createElement(\(dqdiv\(dq);
div.classList = \(dqfoo\(dq; \f[I]// forwarded to classList.value\f[R]

\f[I]// our starting state: <div class=\(dqfoo\(dq></div>\f[R]
console.log(div.outerHTML);

\f[I]// use the classList API to remove and add classes\f[R]
div.classList.remove(\(dqfoo\(dq);
div.classList.add(\(dqanother\-class\(dq);

\f[I]// <div class=\(dqanother\-class\(dq></div>\f[R]
console.log(div.outerHTML);

\f[I]// if visible is set remove it, otherwise add it\f[R]
div.classList.toggle(\(dqvisible\(dq);

\f[I]// add/remove visible, depending on test conditional, i less than 10\f[R]
div.classList.toggle(\(dqvisible\(dq, i < 10);

\f[I]// false\f[R]
console.log(div.classList.contains(\(dqfoo\(dq));

\f[I]// add or remove multiple classes\f[R]
div.classList.add(\(dqfoo\(dq, \(dqbar\(dq, \(dqbaz\(dq);
div.classList.remove(\(dqfoo\(dq, \(dqbar\(dq, \(dqbaz\(dq);

\f[I]// add or remove multiple classes using spread syntax\f[R]
\f[B]const\f[R] cls = [\(dqfoo\(dq, \(dqbar\(dq];
div.classList.add(...cls);
div.classList.remove(...cls);

\f[I]// replace class \(dqfoo\(dq with class \(dqbar\(dq\f[R]
div.classList.replace(\(dqfoo\(dq, \(dqbar\(dq);
.EE
